      <section eId="sec_CC-1829">
        <num>CC 1829</num>
        <heading>1829. Â Subrogation by operation of law</heading>
        <subsection eId="CC-1829__subsec_1">
          <num>(1)</num>
          <content>
            <p>In favor of an obligee who pays another obligee whose right is preferred to his because of a privilege, pledge, mortgage, or security interest;</p>
          </content>
        </subsection>
        <subsection eId="CC-1829__subsec_2">
          <num>(2)</num>
          <content>
            <p>In favor of a purchaser of movable or immovable property who uses the purchase money to pay creditors holding any privilege, pledge, mortgage, or security interest on the property;</p>
          </content>
        </subsection>
        <subsection eId="CC-1829__subsec_3">
          <num>(3)</num>
          <content>
            <p>In favor of an obligor who pays a debt he owes with others or for others and who has recourse against those others as a result of the payment;</p>
          </content>
        </subsection>
        <subsection eId="CC-1829__subsec_4">
          <num>(4)</num>
          <content>
            <p>In favor of a successor who pays estate debts with his own funds; and</p>
          </content>
        </subsection>
        <subsection eId="CC-1829__subsec_5">
          <num>(5)</num>
          <content>
            <p>In the other cases provided by law.</p>
          </content>
        </subsection>
        <authorialNote marker="source">
          <p>Source: https://www.legis.la.gov/legis/Law.aspx?d=109068</p>
        </authorialNote>
      </section>
